                          --AMIGADOS GUIDE V2.6--
                                  FAILAT


   USE:
   Failat displays or sets the failure condition at which a script will be
   terminated.

   PATH:
   Internal

   SYSTEM:
   2.0 (enhanced), 2.1, 3.0

   EXAMPLES:
   1>FAILAT (read current fail limit)
   1>FAILAT 5 (set failure rate at 5)

   NOTES:
   Recommended values:
   5 Warn, 10 Error, 20 Fail
